text: Moonsund archipelago West Estonian archipelago (, also Moonsund archipelago) is a group of Estonian islands located in the Baltic Sea around Väinameri. The total area is about . The archipelago is composed of the islands Saaremaa, Hiiumaa, Muhu, Vormsi and about 900 other smaller islands. == Protected areas== UNESCO established the West Estonian Archipelago Biosphere Reserve in 1990 under the Man and the Biosphere Programme. ==See also== *List of islands of Estonia *Estonian Swedes == References == ==External links== *The Väinameri Sea Estonica Category:Archipelagoes of the Baltic Sea • Category:Biosphere reserves of Estonia Category:Gulf of Riga
